Stir tomato salsa, chipotle salsa, and pineapple preserves in crock of a slow cooker. Add chicken and turn to coat in salsa mixture. Cook on Low until chicken is tender and easily shredded, 3 to 4 hours. Remove chicken to a cutting board; shred with 2 forks. Return shredded chicken to salsa mixture, stir, and continue cooking for 1 hour more.